\pard\plain\ltrpar\qj\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch A flush operation writes the accumulated pixels to a disk file and display.  Disk files will be in the "ppm" file format. ppm files are color image files that have an ascii header with xs and ys image-dimensions and a binary 3-byte pixel format:}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
