\pard\plain\ltrpar\qj\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Display objects hide the organization of pixel memory and its allocation from the application and renderer.  Only applications create, free, and flush Displays.  Display class and size are determined by the application.  }{\s28\f0\fs24\b\lang1033{\*\listtag0}(The size should be same or less than the frame buffer size.)  }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}Pixels are written by the Renderer using the Put call.  Defining the API interfaces makes the application and Renderer library display-independent.  See the disp.cpp file for a complete description of the API.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
